snippet.textDisplay:
Allah tala nay her ek shae m ek mehk rakhi h achi ya buri  kainat ki her ek chez m ek alag si mehk h or her mehk ek dosrae s mukhtalaf h. ise tarha miti ki b ek mehk h,  or us m  sukhi miti ki mehk alag h or gili miti ki mehk alag. amuman her kisi ko gili miti ki kushbu zayad pasand hn. liken sochnay ki bat h q ? or y kushbu insan s q nahi ati ? jab k insan  to paida honay s marnay tak geli miti hi ka hota h. 
sukhi miti hawa k josh per asman tak ko miti ker deti h, apny khak hony ka guruor hota h ya bulandi per jany ki madhoshi; liken pher b us ki mehk geli miti ki mehk per mumtaz nahi. isi tarha jab insan apni ana, jawani, our madhoshi m asman tak to mounhch jata h liken uski ana, grour , or jawani ki madhoshi us m wo mehk nahi la sakty jo geli miti ki ajzi m h. jab  khuda ki rehmat ki bondaen us miti per perti hn to wo khak aker apnay asal s aker lipat jati h. or us ajzi s us m gulmil jati h k kabi wo oper uri hi nahi, ur apnay irdgird ko hazroon miloon tak mehka deti h, y hi haqeeqat insan ki h, jab us per khuda ki rehmat ki nazar hoti h to wo ajzi s girgira k rota h or  apnay asal s miljat h or rab ki bargha m sajda deta h or us ki ajzi ko allah is tarha qabool kerta h k us ki iman ki mehk us k irdgird phela deta h. pher allah apny karam s us m mohbaat , aman or iman ka beech bota h, jo agay chal ker ek phaldar darkht ban jata h or makhool kae khuda k liye niki ka wasela hota h. 
beech insan k zehan m uski soch h ager wo soch musbaat hogi to uska phul  acha hoga ager wo soch manfi hogi to khar k ilawa kuch nahi paeda hoga,  mushkil museebat or takleef m khuda k agay apni ajzi or peshamani k ansoon s tar sajidae m hi humray zehno m musbat soch ati h. or hamri zindagi geli miti ki khushbu ki tarah mehkti h. werna manfi soch m insan asmano per khak chany k ilawa or kuch nai kerta.

snippet.textDisplay:
Kahoon dost se dost ki baat kya kya
Rahi dushmanon se mulaaqaat kya kya
What wondrous secrets should I speak of to the Friend who lives in His friend’s heart?
What moment was spent in the thought of anything but Him?

Wuh ‘ishwe wuh ghamze
wuh naghme wuh jalwe
Talab kar rahe ham- aafaat kya kya
Those heart-stopping glances, those mischievous graces
That rapturous music, that dazzling unveiling
What wondrous calamities we are seeking!

Jahaan mujh ko aaya khayaal aa gaye wuh
Dikhaayi hain dil ne karaamaat kya kya
As soon as His thought appeared, He appeared in my heart
what wondrous miracles the heart has accomplished!

Nah thi guftugu darmiyaan phir bhi un se
Pas-i parda-i dil hui baat kya kya
Though nothing was said to Him face to face
What wondrous conversation occurred behind the curtain of the heart!

Kahoon dost se dost ki baat kya kya
What wondrous secrets should I speak of to the Friend who lives in His friend’s heart?
